column1: I am a down to earth, fairly good looking, fun loving, open minded, professionally qualified wheatish complexion girl with well educated family background. I am loving, caring and responsible for my duties towards my near and dear ones. I love to live life to the fullest, with the attitude "live and let live." Being an artist patience is the main virtue of my life. I am a nature lover and enjoy traveling and hiking. I am passionate about exploring latest digital technology and different areas of creativity. I love to listen music and watching movies. I am modern in my lifestyle and my friends describe me as loyal, honest, patient, compassionate, warm person. Besides this cooking, visiting art exhibitions, museums, science research centers, cultural activities are my never say no interests. I'm looking for someone sincere, intelligent, caring, and genuine person who wish to live life to the fullest, a friend to share a life filled with mutual respect, love, and prosperity. Who would also like to start a family. Someone who is professionally educated, ambitious with strong values, ethics, inner peace and genuine family ties, friendships and relationships. Who would like to be a support to his better half by all means and enjoy the rewards of hard work. Though I am and have open-minded outlook on life, I do give considerable importance to my traditional Hindu values and culture. I believe in Ganesha, and prefer to start my day with the Gayatri Mantra.,"Suitable personality, spiritual, sincere, fun loving, ambitious and full of life, who would be my best friend with trust, respect and a life time commitment as well as desirous of being together in life and raising a lovely family. Looking for partner who would like to grow together personally, professionally and live life fullest.","I come from a moderate Maharashtrian family from Vanjari Community. Ours is a warm and loving close-knit family. My father was a life Insurance Development Officer in Mumbai and my mom is a home-maker. Our upbringing has made us independent and professionally successful in our career. I have three elder sisters who are happily married, financially independent. Having three nephews and two beautiful nieces. Presently, my mother, my younger sister and myself make a small and happy family. We are quite well settled family and believe in simple living and high thinking. Art, literature and social work is in our blood. column1: I am secure & happy with myself, but Life is meant for two. A little bit about myself: I enjoy traveling, reading timeless books which put great flavor into many of my evenings and watching movies that make you wonder for days about whose side you are on. I also enjoy home decor, baking, cooking and celebrating special occasions. I am a self-sufficient, independent and an honest individual that treats others with respect and expect the same in return. column1: I believe that a simple life is best for everyone as it guides you to eliminate the unnecessary things from your life. I portray myself as a simple and a sober person who simplifies everything in order to avoid the complexities of life. By profession I am a CA and currently I am running a CA practicing firm. I am very serious about my work and work hard to achieve the top position. I do my work with complete loyalty and dedication. I am very close to my family and care a lot about them. My mother is a housewife and father is a Sr. Manager of a reputed Engineering firm. After my school education, I completed my B Sc (Honors) from Calcutta University and CA Certificate. Whenever I get time from work I like to do the household works and cook. I also like to drive, listen to music and read novels. I have very few friends and like to spend most of my time with them. My nature is that of a very caring person and I care about my friends a lot.,"Like every girl even I have some desires regarding my life partner. Most importantly he should be a nice human being. I have no problems in marrying a person from any profession. He should be well settled so that he can take care of me properly.

I want my life partner to be well educated and qualified so that he can understand my perspective towards life. Every parent wants their girl to be married in a good family so as mine. My husband should come from a good family background and they must have a decent image in the society.

According to me a there should be transparency between a couple and I want my husband to be honest with me. This way we can avoid unnecessary misunderstandings between us. He should give sheer importance to elders and must respect them. This way I will be able to respect him as well as his family and the elderly members.

My major weakness is that I am very emotional so I want my life partner to know about it. He should take care of this fact. I want him to understand me and make me strong enough to face the world. If he is like this then I will give him all my love.
,,39 to 43,06 Jan 1974,21:20:00,India,Kolkata,Average,Doesn't Matter,,Baidya,,,,Fair ,Doesn't Matter,Daughter,CA (Chartered Accountant),39 yrs, 5ft 4in,

column1: I belong to a modernised traditional family. I along with my siblings { 2 } have seen most of the world thanks to my parents.I was student for 5 years in Hongkong and later moved to Bangalore . I obtained my BA from Mt.Carmel College,Bangalore. Went { came? } to the US for post graduate Studies { MS in Child Edu M.S in Teacher Cert } and have been in the US since 1998. After working fro sometime decided to get an MBA from Drexel Univ in Philadelphia.Now in the last lap of 6 months.. Wiil get that MBA in May 2009.Despite the few years in the USA I am yet a South Indian with some sheen from the exposure to US and my travels. I have one sister elder who is a PhD from Bryn Mawr College and she is married to Dr. Jayaraman. One brother (younger ) with an M.S ( Bioinfomatics ) and an M.S (biomedical ) from the Univ.Of Pennsylvania is employed with Childrens Hosp. Of Philadelphia.. Father ( an MBA from Wharton School, Univ. Of Penn ) now retired from the post of Regional Director of an American Pharma. company. Parents now live in Cochin, Kerala. Oh Yes Mother.. she is the greatest Homemaker!. We { parents } want to add the following since on more than one occasion we were informed of the concern due to Nirmala's visa status and the financial implications. This is but natural and this we overlooked. Hence we state the obvious and that is that we the parents stand behind our Nirmala. Nirmala has an F1 Visa now and she will move on to OPT { practical training } Visa for one year. During this period she wiil get her H1 Visa.
